Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulders. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces forward. Press it overhead by extending the elbow.

exercises.name: Kipping Muscle Up
exercises.hint: Grip the rings using a false grip, with the base of your palms on top of the rings.

exercises.name: Knee Across The Body
exercises.hint: Lie down on the floor with your right leg straight. Bend your left leg and lower it across your body, holding the knee down toward the floor with your right hand. (The knee doesn't need to touch the floor if you're tight.)

exercises.name: Knee Circles
exercises.hint: Stand with your legs together and hands by your waist.

exercises.name: Knee/Hip Raise On Parallel Bars
exercises.hint: Position your body on the vertical leg raise bench so that your forearms are resting on the pads next to the torso and holding on to the handles. Your arms will be bent at a 90 degree angle.

exercises.name: Knee Tuck Jump
exercises.hint: Begin in a comfortable standing position with your knees slightly bent. Hold your hands in front of you, palms down with your fingertips together at chest height. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Kneeling Arm Drill
exercises.hint: This drill helps increase arm efficiency during the run. Begin kneeling, left foot in front, right knee down. Apply pressure through the front heel to keep your glutes and hamstrings activated.

exercises.name: Kneeling Cable Crunch With Alternating Oblique Twists
exercises.hint: Connect a rope attachment to a high pulley cable and position a mat on the floor in front of it.

exercises.name: Kneeling Cable Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Place a bench sideways in front of a high pulley machine.

exercises.name: Kneeling Forearm Stretch
exercises.hint: Start by kneeling on a mat with your palms flat and your fingers pointing back toward your knees.

exercises.name: Kneeling High Pulley Row
exercises.hint: Select the appropriate weight using a pulley that is above your head. Attach a rope to the cable and kneel a couple of feet away, holding the rope out in front of you with both arms extended. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Kneeling Hip Flexor
exercises.hint: Kneel on a mat and bring your right knee up so the bottom of your foot is on the floor and extend your left leg out behind you so the top of your foot is on the floor.

exercises.name: Kneeling Single-Arm High Pulley Row
exercises.hint: Attach a single handle to a high pulley and make your weight selection.

exercises.name: Kneeling Squat
exercises.hint: Set the bar to the proper height in a power rack. Kneel behind the bar; it may be beneficial to put a mat down to pad your knees. Slide under the bar, racking it across the back of your shoulders. Your shoulder blades should be retracted and the bar tight across your back. Unrack the weight.

exercises.name: Landmine 180's
exercises.hint: Position a bar into a landmine or securely anchor it in a corner. Load the bar to an appropriate weight.

exercises.name: Landmine Linear Jammer
exercises.hint: Position a bar into landmine or, lacking one, securely anchor it in a corner. Load the bar to an appropriate weight and position the handle attachment on the bar.

exercises.name: Lateral Bound
exercises.hint: Assume a half squat position facing 90 degrees from your direction of travel. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lateral Box Jump
exercises.hint: Assume a comfortable standing position, with a short box positioned next to you. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lateral Cone Hops
exercises.hint: Position a number of cones in a row several feet apart.

exercises.name: Lateral Raise - With Bands
exercises.hint: To begin, stand on an exercise band so that tension begins at arm's length. Grasp the handles using a pronated (palms facing your thighs) grip that is slightly less than shoulder width. The handles should be resting on the sides of your thighs. Your arms should be extended with a slight bend at the elbows and your back should be straight. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Latissimus Dorsi-SMR
exercises.hint: While lying on the floor, place a foam roll under your back and to one side, just behind your arm pit. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leg Extensions
exercises.hint: For this exercise you will need to use a leg extension machine. First choose your weight and sit on the machine with your legs under the pad (feet pointed forward) and the hands holding the side bars. This will be your starting position. Tip: You will need to adjust the pad so that it falls on top of your lower leg (just above your feet). Also, make sure that your legs form a 90-degree angle between the lower and upper leg. If the angle is less than 90-degrees then that means the knee is over the toes which in turn creates undue stress at the knee joint. If the machine is designed that way, either look for another machine or just make sure that when you start executing the exercise you stop going down once you hit the 90-degree angle.

exercises.name: Leg Lift
exercises.hint: While standing up straight with both feet next to each other at around shoulder width, grab a sturdy surface such as the sides of a squat rack or the top of a chair to brace yourself and keep balance.

exercises.name: Leg-Over Floor Press
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor with one kettlebell in place on your chest, holding it by the handle. Extend leg on working side over leg on non-working side.Your free arm can be extended out to your side for support.

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.hint: Using a leg press machine, sit down on the machine and place your legs on the platform directly in front of you at a medium (shoulder width) foot stance. (Note: For the purposes of this discussion we will use the medium stance described above which targets overall development; however you can choose any of the three stances described in the foot positioning section).

exercises.name: Leg Pull-In
exercises.hint: Lie on an exercise mat with your legs extended and your hands either palms facing down next to you or under your glutes. Tip: My preference is with the hands next to me. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leg-Up Hamstring Stretch
exercises.hint: Lie flat on your back, bend one knee, and put that foot flat on the floor to stabilize your spine.

exercises.name: Leverage Chest Press
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat for your height. The handles should be near the bottom or middle of the pectorals at the beginning of the motion.

exercises.name: Leverage Deadlift
exercises.hint: Load the pins to an appropriate weight. Position yourself directly between the handles. Grasp the bottom handles with a comfortable grip, and then lower your hips as you take a breath. Look forward with your head and keep your chest up. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage Decline Chest Press
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat for your height. The handles should be near the bottom of the pectorals at the beginning of the motion. Your chest and head should be up and your shoulder blades retracted. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage High Row
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat height so that you can just reach the handles above you. Adjust the knee pad to help keep you down. Grasp the handles with a pronated grip. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage Incline Chest Press
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat for your height. The handles should be near the top of the pectorals at the beginning of the motion. Your chest and head should be up and your shoulder blades retracted. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage Iso Row
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat height so that the handles are at chest level. Grasp the handles with either a neutral or pronated grip. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage Shoulder Press
exercises.hint: Load an appropriate weight onto the pins and adjust the seat for your height. The handles should be near the top of the shoulders at the beginning of the motion. Your chest and head should be up and handles held with a pronated grip. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Leverage Shrug
exercises.hint: Load the pins to an appropriate weight. Position yourself directly between the handles.

exercises.name: Linear 3-Part Start Technique
exercises.hint: This drill helps you accelerate as quickly as possible into a sprint from a dead stop. It helps to use a line to start from. Begin with two feet on the line. Place your left foot with the toe next to your right ankle. Place your right foot 4-6 inches behind the left.

exercises.name: Linear Acceleration Wall Drill
exercises.hint: Lean at around 45 degrees against a wall. Your feet should be together, glutes contracted.

exercises.name: Linear Depth Jump
exercises.hint: You will need two boxes or benches spaced a few feet away from each other. Begin by standing on one box facing towards the other platform.

exercises.name: Log Lift
exercises.hint: Begin standing with the log in front of you. Grasp the handles, and begin to clean the log. As you are bent over to start the clean, attempt to get the log as high as possible, pulling it into your chest. Extend through the hips and knees to bring it up to complete the clean.

exercises.name: London Bridges
exercises.hint: Attach a climbing rope to a high beam or cross member. Below it, ensure that the smith machine bar is locked in place with the safeties and cannot move. Alternatively, a secure box could also be utilized.

exercises.name: Looking At Ceiling
exercises.hint: Kneel on the floor, holding your heels with both hands.

exercises.name: Low Cable Crossover
exercises.hint: To move into the starting position, place the pulleys at the low position, select the resistance to be used and grasp a handle in each hand.

exercises.name: Low Cable Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Select the desired weight and lay down face up on the bench of a seated row machine that has a rope attached to it. Your head should be pointing towards the attachment.

exercises.name: Low Pulley Row To Neck
exercises.hint: Sit on a low pulley row machine with a rope attachment.

exercises.name: Lower Back Curl
exercises.hint: Lie on your stomach with your arms out to your sides. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lower Back-SMR
exercises.hint: In a seated position, place a foam roll under your lower back. Cross your arms in front of you and protract your shoulders. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lunge Pass Through
exercises.hint: Stand with your torso upright holding a kettlebell in your right hand. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lunge Sprint
exercises.hint: Adjust a bar in a Smith machine to an appropriate height. Position yourself under the bar, racking it across the back of your shoulders. Unrack the bar, and then split your feet, moving one foot forward and one foot back. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Bent Leg Groin
exercises.hint: Lie on your back with your knees bent and the soles of the feet pressed together. Have your partner hold your knees. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Cable Curl
exercises.hint: Grab a straight bar or E-Z bar attachment that is attached to the low pulley with both hands, using an underhand (palms facing up) shoulder-width grip.

exercises.name: Lying Cambered Barbell Row
exercises.hint: Place a cambered bar underneath an exercise bench.

exercises.name: Lying Close-Grip Bar Curl On High Pulley
exercises.hint: Place a flat bench in front of a high pulley or lat pulldown machine.

exercises.name: Lying Close-Grip Barbell Triceps Extension Behind The Head
exercises.hint: While holding a barbell or EZ Curl bar with a pronated grip (palms facing forward), lie on your back on a flat bench with your head close to the end of the bench. Tip: If you are holding a barbell grab it using a shoulder-width grip and if you are using an E-Z Bar grab it on the inner handles.

exercises.name: Lying Close-Grip Barbell Triceps Press To Chin
exercises.hint: While holding a barbell or EZ Curl bar with a pronated grip (palms facing forward), lie on your back on a flat bench with your head off the end of the bench. Tip: If you are holding a barbell grab it using a shoulder-width grip and if you are using an E-Z Bar grab it on the inner handles.

exercises.name: Lying Crossover
exercises.hint: Lie on your back with your legs extended.

exercises.name: Lying Dumbbell Tricep Extension
exercises.hint: Lie on a flat bench while holding two dumbbells directly in front of you. Your arms should be fully extended at a 90-degree angle from your torso and the floor. The palms should be facing in and the elbows should be tucked in. This is the starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Face Down Plate Neck Resistance
exercises.hint: Lie face down with your whole body straight on a flat bench while holding a weight plate behind your head. Tip: You will need to position yourself so that your shoulders are slightly above the end of a flat bench in order for the upper chest, neck and face to be off the bench. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Face Up Plate Neck Resistance
exercises.hint: Lie face up with your whole body straight on a flat bench while holding a weight plate on top of your forehead. Tip: You will need to position yourself so that your shoulders are slightly above the end of a flat bench in order for the traps, neck and head to be off the bench. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Glute
exercises.hint: Lie on your back with your partner kneeling beside you.

exercises.name: Lying Hamstring
exercises.hint: Lie on your back with your legs extended. Your partner should be kneeling beside you. Raise one leg up towards the ceiling and have your partner hold the ankle. Your partner can use their shoulder to brace your leg if necessary. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying High Bench Barbell Curl
exercises.hint: Lie face forward on a tall flat bench while holding a barbell with a supinated grip (palms facing up). Tip: If you are holding a barbell grab it using a shoulder-width grip and if you are using an E-Z Bar grab it on the inner handles. Your upper body should be positioned in a way that the upper chest is over the end of the bench and the barbell is hanging in front of you with the arms extended and perpendicular to the floor. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Machine Squat
exercises.hint: Adjust the leg machine to a height that will allow you to get inside it with your knees bent and the thighs slightly below parallel.

exercises.name: Lying One-Arm Lateral Raise
exercises.hint: While holding a dumbbell in one hand, lay with your chest down on a flat bench. The other hand can be used to hold to the leg of the bench for stability.

exercises.name: Lying Prone Quadriceps
exercises.hint: Lay face down on the floor with your partner kneeling beside you. Flex one knee and raise that leg off the ground, attempting to touch your glutes with your foot. Your partner should hold the knee and ankle. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Lying Rear Delt Raise
exercises.hint: While holding a dumbbell in each hand, lay with your chest down on a flat bench.

exercises.name: Lying Supine Dumbbell Curl
exercises.hint: Lie down on a flat bench face up while holding a dumbbell in each arm on top of your thighs.

exercises.name: Lying T-Bar Row
exercises.hint: Load up the T-bar Row Machine with the desired weight and adjust the leg height so that your upper chest is at the top of the pad. Tip: In some machines all you can do is stand on the appropriate step that allows you to be at a height that has the upper chest at the top of the pad.

exercises.name: Lying Triceps Press
exercises.hint: Lie on a flat bench with either an e-z bar (my preference) or a straight bar placed on the floor behind your head and your feet on the floor.

exercises.name: Machine Bench Press
exercises.hint: Sit down on the Chest Press Machine and select the weight.

exercises.name: Machine Bicep Curl
exercises.hint: Adjust the seat to the appropriate height and make your weight selection. Place your upper arms against the pads and grasp the handles. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Machine Preacher Curls
exercises.hint: Sit down on the Preacher Curl Machine and select the weight.

exercises.name: Machine Shoulder (Military) Press
exercises.hint: Sit down on the Shoulder Press Machine and select the weight.

exercises.name: Machine Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Adjust the seat to the appropriate height and make your weight selection. Place your upper arms against the pads and grasp the handles. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
exercises.hint: You will need a partner for this exercise. Lacking one, this movement can be performed against a wall.

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Scoop Throw
exercises.hint: Assume a semisquat stance with a medicine ball in your hands. Your arms should hang so the ball is near your feet.

exercises.name: Middle Back Shrug
exercises.hint: Lie facedown on an incline bench while holding a dumbbell in each hand. Your arms should be fully extended hanging down and pointing towards the floor. The palms of your hands should be facing each other. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Middle Back Stretch
exercises.hint: Stand so your feet are shoulder width apart and your hands are on your hips.

exercises.name: Mixed Grip Chin
exercises.hint: Using a spacing that is just about 1 inch wider than shoulder width, grab a pull-up bar with the palms of one hand facing forward and the palms of the other hand facing towards you. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Monster Walk
exercises.hint: Place a band around both ankles and another around both knees. There should be enough tension that they are tight when your feet are shoulder width apart.

exercises.name: Mountain Climbers
exercises.hint: Begin in a pushup position, with your weight supported by your hands and toes. Flexing the knee and hip, bring one leg until the knee is approximately under the hip. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Moving Claw Series
exercises.hint: This move helps prepare your running form to help you excel at sprinting. As you run, be sure to flex the knee, aiming to kick your glutes as the hip extends.

exercises.name: Muscle Snatch
exercises.hint: Begin with a loaded barbell held at the mid thigh position with a wide grip. The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Muscle Up
exercises.hint: Grip the rings using a false grip, with the base of your palms on top of the rings. Initiate a pull up by pulling the elbows down to your side, flexing the elbows.

exercises.name: Narrow Stance Hack Squats
exercises.hint: Place the back of your torso against the back pad of the machine and hook your shoulders under the shoulder pads provided.

exercises.name: Narrow Stance Leg Press
exercises.hint: Using a leg press machine, sit down on the machine and place your legs on the platform directly in front of you at a less-than-shoulder-width narrow stance with the toes slightly pointed out. Your feet should be around 3 inches or less apart. Tip: Keep your head up at all times and also maintain the back on the pad at all times.

exercises.name: Narrow Stance Squats
exercises.hint: This exercise is best performed inside a squat rack for safety purposes. To begin, first set the bar on a rack that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck) across it.

exercises.name: Natural Glute Ham Raise
exercises.hint: Using the leg pad of a lat pulldown machine or a preacher bench, position yourself so that your ankles are under the pads, knees on the seat, and you are facing away from the machine. You should be upright and maintaining good posture.

exercises.name: Neck Press
exercises.hint: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a medium-width grip (a grip that creates a 90-degree angle in the middle of the movement between the forearms and the upper arms), lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over your neck with your arms locked. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Neck-SMR
exercises.hint: Using a muscle roller or a rolling pin, place the roller behind your head and against your neck. Make sure that you do not place the roller directly against the spine, but turned slightly so that the roller is pressed against the muscles to either side of the spine. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Oblique Crunches
exercises.hint: Lie flat on the floor with your lower back pressed to the ground. For this exercise, you will need to put one hand beside your head and the other to the side against the floor.

exercises.name: Oblique Crunches - On The Floor
exercises.hint: Start out by lying on your right side with your legs lying on top of each other. Make sure your knees are bent a little bit.

exercises.name: Olympic Squat
exercises.hint: Begin with a barbell supported on top of the traps. The chest should be up, and the head facing forward. Adopt a hip width stance with the feet turned out as needed.

exercises.name: On-Your-Back Quad Stretch
exercises.hint: Lie on a flat bench or step, and hang one leg and arm over the side.

exercises.name: On Your Side Quad Stretch
exercises.hint: Start off by lying on your right side, with your right knee bent at a 90-degree angle resting on the floor in front of you (this stabilizes the torso).

exercises.name: One Arm Against Wall
exercises.hint: From a standing position, place a bent arm against a wall or doorway.

exercises.name: One Arm Chin-Up
exercises.hint: For this exercise, start out by placing a towel around a chin up bar.

exercises.name: One Arm Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.hint: Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand on top of your thigh.

exercises.name: One Arm Dumbbell Preacher Curl
exercises.hint: Grab a dumbbell with the right arm and place the upper arm on top of the preacher bench or the incline bench. The dumbbell should be held at shoulder length. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Dumbbell Row
exercises.hint: Choose a flat bench and place a dumbbell on each side of it.

exercises.name: One-Arm Flat Bench Dumbbell Flye
exercises.hint: Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand resting on top of your thigh. The palm of your hand with the dumbbell in it should be at a neutral grip.

exercises.name: One Arm Floor Press
exercises.hint: Lie down on a flat surface with your back pressing against the floor or an exercise mat. Make sure your knees are bent.

exercises.name: One-Arm High-Pulley Cable Side Bends
exercises.hint: Connect a standard handle to a tower. Move cable to highest pulley position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Incline Lateral Raise
exercises.hint: Lie down sideways on an incline bench press with a dumbbell in the hand. Make sure the shoulder is pressing against the incline bench and the arm is lying across your body with the palm around your navel.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Clean
exercises.hint: Place a kettlebell between your feet. As you bend down to grab the kettlebell, push your butt back and keep your eyes looking forward.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Clean and Jerk
exercises.hint: Hold a kettlebell by the handle.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Jerk
exercises.hint: Hold a kettlebell by the handle. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces forward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Military Press To The Side
exercises.hint: Clean a kettlebell to your shoulder. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces inward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Para Press
exercises.hint: Clean a kettlebell to your shoulder. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces forward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Push Press
exercises.hint: Hold a kettlebell by the handle. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces forward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Row
exercises.hint: Place a kettlebell in front of your feet. Bend your knees slightly and then push your butt out as much as possible as you bend over to get in the starting position. Grab the kettlebell and pull it to your stomach, retracting your shoulder blade and flexing the elbow. Keep your back straight. Lower and repeat.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Snatch
exercises.hint: Place a kettlebell between your feet. Bend your knees and push your butt back to get in the proper starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Split Jerk
exercises.hint: Hold a kettlebell by the handle. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so, so that the palm faces forward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Kettlebell Split Snatch
exercises.hint: Hold a kettlebell in one hand by the handle.

exercises.name: One-Arm Long Bar Row
exercises.hint: Position a bar into a landmine or in a corner to keep it from moving. Load an appropriate weight onto your end.

exercises.name: One-Arm Medicine Ball Slam
exercises.hint: Start in a standing position with a staggered, athletic stance. Hold a medicine ball in one hand, on the same side as your back leg. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One-Arm Open Palm Kettlebell Clean
exercises.hint: Place one kettlebell between your feet.

exercises.name: One-Arm Overhead Kettlebell Squats
exercises.hint: Clean and press a kettlebell with one arm. Clean the kettlebell to your shoulder by extending through the legs and hips as you pull the kettlebell towards your shoulder. Rotate your wrist as you do so. Press the weight overhead by extending through the elbow.This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: One Arm Pronated Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Lie flat on a bench while holding a dumbbell at arms length. Your arm should be perpendicular to your body. The palm of your hand should be facing towards your feet as a pronated grip is required to perform this exercise.

exercises.name: One-Arm Side Deadlift
exercises.hint: Stand to the side of a barbell next to its center. Bend your knees and lower your body until you are able to reach the barbell.

exercises.name: One-Arm Side Laterals
exercises.hint: Pick a dumbbell and place it in one of your hands. Your non lifting hand should be used to grab something steady such as an incline bench press. Lean towards your lifting arm and away from the hand that is gripping the incline bench as this will allow you to keep your balance.

exercises.name: One Arm Supinated Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Lie flat on a bench while holding a dumbbell at arms length. Your arm should be perpendicular to your body. The palm of your hand should be facing towards your face as a supinated grip is required to perform this exercise.

exercises.name: One Half Locust
exercises.hint: Lie facedown on the floor.

exercises.name: One Handed Hang
exercises.hint: Grab onto a chinup bar with one hand, using a pronated grip. Keep your feet on the floor or a step. Allow the majority of your weight to hang from that hand, while keeping your feet on the ground. Hold for 10-20 seconds and switch sides.

exercises.name: One Knee To Chest
exercises.hint: Start off by lying on the floor.

exercises.name: One Leg Barbell Squat
exercises.hint: Start by standing about 2 to 3 feet in front of a flat bench with your back facing the bench. Have a barbell in front of you on the floor. Tip: Your feet should be shoulder width apart from each other.

exercises.name: One-Legged Cable Kickback
exercises.hint: Hook a leather ankle cuff to a low cable pulley and then attach the cuff to your ankle.

exercises.name: Open Palm Kettlebell Clean
exercises.hint: Place one kettlebell between your feet. Clean the kettlebell by extending through the legs and hips as you raise the kettlebell towards your shoulders.

exercises.name: Otis-Up
exercises.hint: Secure your feet and lay back on the floor. Your knees should be bent. Hold a weight with both hands to your chest. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Overhead Cable Curl
exercises.hint: To begin, set a weight that is comfortable on each side of the pulley machine. Note: Make sure that the amount of weight selected is the same on each side.

exercises.name: Overhead Lat
exercises.hint: Sit upright on the floor with your partner behind you. Raise one arm straight up, and flex the elbow, attempting to touch your hand to your back. Your parner should hold your tricep and wrist. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Overhead Slam
exercises.hint: Hold a medine ball with both hands and stand with your feet at shoulder width. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Overhead Squat
exercises.hint: Start out by having a barbell in front of you on the floor. Your feet should be wider than shoulder width apart from each other.

exercises.name: Overhead Stretch
exercises.hint: Standing straight up, lace your fingers together and open your palms to the ceiling. Keep your shoulders down as you extend your arms up.

exercises.name: Overhead Triceps
exercises.hint: Sit upright on the floor with your partner behind you. Raise one arm straight up, and flex the elbow, attempting to touch your hand to your back. Your parner should hold your elbow and wrist. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Pallof Press
exercises.hint: Connect a standard handle to a tower, and—if possible—position the cable to shoulder height. If not, a low pulley will suffice.

exercises.name: Pallof Press With Rotation
exercises.hint: Connect a standard handle to a tower, and position the cable to shoulder height.

exercises.name: Palms-Down Dumbbell Wrist Curl Over A Bench
exercises.hint: Start out by placing two dumbbells on one side of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Palms-Down Wrist Curl Over A Bench
exercises.hint: Start out by placing a barbell on one side of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Palms-Up Barbell Wrist Curl Over A Bench
exercises.hint: Start out by placing a barbell on one side of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Palms-Up Dumbbell Wrist Curl Over A Bench
exercises.hint: Start out by placing two dumbbells on one side of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Parallel Bar Dip
exercises.hint: Stand between a set of parallel bars. Place a hand on each bar, and then take a small jump to help you get into the starting position with your arms locked out.

exercises.name: Pelvic Tilt Into Bridge
exercises.hint: Lie down with your feet on the floor, heels directly under your knees.

exercises.name: Peroneals-SMR
exercises.hint: Lay on your side, supporting your weight on your forearm and on a foam roller placed on the outside of your lower leg. Your upper leg can either be on top of your lower leg, or you can cross it in front of you. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Peroneals Stretch
exercises.hint: In a seated position, loop a belt, rope, or band around one foot. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Physioball Hip Bridge
exercises.hint: Lay on a ball so that your upper back is on the ball with your hips unsupported. Both feet should be flat on the floor, hip width apart or wider. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Piriformis-SMR
exercises.hint: Sit with your buttocks on top of a foam roll. Bend your knees, and then cross one leg so that the ankle is over the knee. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.hint: Get into a prone position on the floor, supporting your weight on your toes and your forearms. Your arms are bent and directly below the shoulder.

exercises.name: Plate Pinch
exercises.hint: Grab two wide-rimmed plates and put them together with the smooth sides facing outward

exercises.name: Plate Twist
exercises.hint: Lie down on the floor or an exercise mat with your legs fully extended and your upper body upright. Grab the plate by its sides with both hands out in front of your abdominals with your arms slightly bent.

exercises.name: Platform Hamstring Slides
exercises.hint: For this movement a wooden floor or similar is needed. Lay on your back with your legs extended. Place a gym towel or a light weight underneath your heel. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Plie Dumbbell Squat
exercises.hint: Hold a dumbbell at the base with both hands and stand straight up. Move your legs so that they are wider than shoulder width apart from each other with your knees slightly bent.

exercises.name: Plyo Kettlebell Pushups
exercises.hint: Place a kettlebell on the floor. Place yourself in a pushup position, on your toes with one hand on the ground and one hand holding the kettlebell, with your elbows extended. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Plyo Push-up
exercises.hint: Move into a prone position on the floor, supporting your weight on your hands and toes.

exercises.name: Posterior Tibialis Stretch
exercises.hint: In a seated position, loop a belt, rope, or band around one foot. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Power Clean
exercises.hint: Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart and toes pointing out slightly.

exercises.name: Power Clean from Blocks
exercises.hint: With a barbell on boxes of the desired height, take a grip just outside the legs. Lower your hips with the weight focused on the heels, back straight, head facing forward, chest up, with your shoulders just in front of the bar. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Power Jerk
exercises.hint: Standing with the weight racked on the front of the shoulders, begin with the dip. With your feet directly under your hips, flex the knees without moving the hips backward. Go down only slightly, and reverse direction as powerfully as possible.

exercises.name: Power Partials
exercises.hint: Stand up with your torso upright and a dumbbell on each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso.

exercises.name: Power Snatch
exercises.hint: Begin with a loaded barbell on the floor. The bar should be close to or touching the shins, and a wide grip should be taken on the bar. The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Power Snatch from Blocks
exercises.hint: Begin with a loaded barbell on boxes or stands of the desired height. A wide grip should be taken on the bar. The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar, with the elbows pointed out. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Power Stairs
exercises.hint: In the power stairs, implements are moved up a staircase. For training purposes, these can be performed with a tire or box.

exercises.name: Preacher Curl
exercises.hint: To perform this movement you will need a preacher bench and an E-Z bar. Grab the E-Z curl bar at the close inner handle (either have someone hand you the bar which is preferable or grab the bar from the front bar rest provided by most preacher benches). The palm of your hands should be facing forward and they should be slightly tilted inwards due to the shape of the bar.

exercises.name: Preacher Hammer Dumbbell Curl
exercises.hint: Place the upper part of both arms on top of the preacher bench as you hold a dumbbell in each hand with the palms facing each other (neutral grip).

exercises.name: Press Sit-Up
exercises.hint: To begin, lie down on a bench with a barbell resting on your chest. Position your legs so they are secure on the extension of the abdominal bench. This is the starting position.

exercises.name: Prone Manual Hamstring
exercises.hint: You will need a partner for this exercise. Lay face down with your legs straight. Your assistant will place their hand on your heel.

exercises.name: Prowler Sprint
exercises.hint: Place your sled on an appropriate surface, loaded to a suitable weight. The sled should provide enough resistance to require effort, but not so heavy that you are significantly slowed down.

exercises.name: Pull Through
exercises.hint: Begin standing a few feet in front of a low pulley with a rope or handle attached. Face away from the machine, straddling the cable, with your feet set wide apart.

exercises.name: Pullups
exercises.hint: Grab the pull-up bar with the palms facing forward using the prescribed grip. Note on grips: For a wide grip, your hands need to be spaced out at a distance wider than your shoulder width. For a medium grip, your hands need to be spaced out at a distance equal to your shoulder width and for a close grip at a distance smaller than your shoulder width.

exercises.name: Push Press - Behind the Neck
exercises.hint: Standing with the weight racked on the back of the shoulders, begin with the dip. With your feet directly under your hips, flex the knees without moving the hips backward. Go down only slightly, and reverse direction as powerfully as possible. Drive through the heels create as much speed and force as possible, moving the bar in a vertical path.

exercises.name: Push Up to Side Plank
exercises.hint: Get into pushup position on the toes with your hands just outside of shoulder width.

exercises.name: Push-Up Wide
exercises.hint: With your hands wide apart, support your body on your toes and hands in a plank position. Your elbows should be extended and your body straight. Do not allow your hips to sag. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Push-Ups - Close Triceps Position
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor face down and place your hands closer than shoulder width for a close hand position. Make sure that you are holding your torso up at arms' length.

exercises.name: Push-Ups With Feet Elevated
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor face down and place your hands about 36 inches apart from each other holding your torso up at arms length.

exercises.name: Push-Ups With Feet On An Exercise Ball
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor face down and place your hands about 36 inches apart from each other holding your torso up at arms length.

exercises.name: Pushups
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor face down and place your hands about 36 inches apart while holding your torso up at arms length.

exercises.name: Pushups (Close and Wide Hand Positions)
exercises.hint: Lie on the floor face down and body straight with your toes on the floor and the hands wider than shoulder width for a wide hand position and closer than shoulder width for a close hand position. Make sure you are holding your torso up at arms length.

exercises.name: Pyramid
exercises.hint: Start off by rolling your torso forward onto the ball so your hips rest on top of the ball and become the highest point of your body.

exercises.name: Quad Stretch
exercises.hint: Lay on your side. Loop a belt, rope, or band around your top foot. Flex the knee and extend your hip, attempting to touch your glutes with your foot, and holding the belt with your hands. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Quadriceps-SMR
exercises.hint: Lay facedown on the floor with your weight supported by your hands or forearms. Place a foam roll underneath one leg on the quadriceps, and keep the foot off of the ground. Make sure to relax the leg as much as possible. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Quick Leap
exercises.hint: You will need a box for this exerise.

exercises.name: Rack Delivery
exercises.hint: This drill teaches the delivery of the barbell to the rack position on the shoulders. Begin holding a bar in the scarecrow position, with the upper arms parallel to the floor, and the forearms hanging down. Use a hook grip, with your fingers wrapped over your thumbs.

exercises.name: Rack Pull with Bands
exercises.hint: Set up in a power rack with the bar on the pins. The pins should be set to the desired point; just below the knees, just above, or in the mid thigh position. Attach bands to the base of the rack, or secure them with dumbbells. Attach the other end to the bar. You may need to choke the bands to provide tension.

exercises.name: Rack Pulls
exercises.hint: Set up in a power rack with the bar on the pins. The pins should be set to the desired point; just below the knees, just above, or in the mid thigh position. Position yourself against the bar in proper deadlifting position. Your feet should be under your hips, your grip shoulder width, back arched, and hips back to engage the hamstrings. Since the weight is typically heavy, you may use a mixed grip, a hook grip, or use straps to aid in holding the weight.

exercises.name: Rear Leg Raises
exercises.hint: Place yourself on your hands knees on an exercise mat. Your head should be looking forward and the bend of the knees should create a 90-degree angle between the hamstrings and the calves. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Recumbent Bike
exercises.hint: To begin, seat yourself on the bike and adjust the seat to your height.

exercises.name: Return Push from Stance
exercises.hint: You will need a partner for this drill.

exercises.name: Reverse Band Box Squat
exercises.hint: Begin in a power rack with a box at the appropriate height behind you. Set up the bands either on band pegs or attached to the top of the rack, ensuring they will be directly above the bar during the squat. Attach the other end to the bar.

exercises.name: Reverse Band Deadlift
exercises.hint: Set the bar up in a power rack. Attach bands to the top of the rack, using either bands pegs or the frame itself. Attach the other end of the bands to the bar.

exercises.name: Reverse Band Power Squat
exercises.hint: Begin in a power rack with the pins and bar set at the appropriate height. After loading the bar, attach bands to the top of the rack, using either pegs or the frame itself. Attach the other end of the bands to the bar.

exercises.name: Reverse Band Sumo Deadlift
exercises.hint: Begin with a bar loaded on the floor inside of a power rack. Attach bands to the top of the rack, using either pegs or the frame itself. Attach the other end to the barbell.

exercises.name: Reverse Barbell Curl
exercises.hint: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a barbell at shoulder width with the elbows close to the torso. The palm of your hands should be facing down (pronated grip). This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Reverse Barbell Preacher Curls
exercises.hint: Grab an EZ-bar using a shoulder width and palms down (pronated) grip.

exercises.name: Reverse Cable Curl
exercises.hint: Stand up with your torso upright while holding a bar attachment that is attached to a low pulley using a pronated (palms down) and shoulder width grip. Make sure also that you keep the elbows close to the torso. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Reverse Crunch
exercises.hint: Lie down on the floor with your legs fully extended and arms to the side of your torso with the palms on the floor. Your arms should be stationary for the entire exercise.

exercises.name: Reverse Flyes
exercises.hint: To begin, lie down on an incline bench with the chest and stomach pressing against the incline. Have the dumbbells in each hand with the palms facing each other (neutral grip).

exercises.name: Reverse Flyes With External Rotation
exercises.hint: To begin, lie down on an incline bench set at a 30-degree angle with the chest and stomach pressing against the incline.

exercises.name: Reverse Grip Bent-Over Rows
exercises.hint: Stand erect while holding a barbell with a supinated grip (palms facing up).

exercises.name: Reverse Grip Triceps Pushdown
exercises.hint: Start by setting a bar attachment (straight or e-z) on a high pulley machine.

exercises.name: Reverse Hyperextension
exercises.hint: Place your feet between the pads after loading an appropriate weight. Lay on the top pad, allowing your hips to hang off the back, while grasping the handles to hold your position.

exercises.name: Reverse Machine Flyes
exercises.hint: Adjust the handles so that they are fully to the rear. Make an appropriate weight selection and adjust the seat height so the handles are at shoulder level. Grasp the handles with your hands facing inwards. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Reverse Plate Curls
exercises.hint: Start by standing straight with a weighted plate held by both hands and arms fully extended. Use a pronated grip (palms facing down) and make sure your fingers grab the rough side of the plate while your thumb grabs the smooth side. Note: For the best results, grab the weighted plate at an 11:00 and 1:00 o'clock position.

exercises.name: Reverse Triceps Bench Press
exercises.hint: Lie back on a flat bench. Using a close, supinated grip (around shoulder width), lift the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked extended in front of you and perpendicular to the floor. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Rhomboids-SMR
exercises.hint: Lay down with your back on the floor. Place a foam roll underneath your upper back, and cross your arms in front of you, protracting your shoulders. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Rickshaw Carry
exercises.hint: Position the frame at the starting point, and load with the appropriate weight. Standing in the center of the frame, begin by gripping the handles and driving through your heels to lift the frame. Ensure your chest and head are up and your back is straight.

exercises.name: Rickshaw Deadlift
exercises.hint: Load the frame with the desired weight. Center yourself between the handles. You feet should be about hip width apart. Bend at the hips to grip the handles, allowing your shoulder blades to protract.

exercises.name: Ring Dips
exercises.hint: Grip a ring in each hand, and then take a small jump to help you get into the starting position with your arms locked out.

exercises.name: Rocket Jump
exercises.hint: Begin in a relaxed stance with your feet shoulder width apart and hold your arms close to the body.

exercises.name: Rocking Standing Calf Raise
exercises.hint: This exercise is best performed inside a squat rack for safety purposes. To begin, first set the bar on a rack that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place it on the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck).

exercises.name: Rocky Pull-Ups/Pulldowns
exercises.hint: Grab the pull-up bar with the palms facing forward using a wide grip.

exercises.name: Romanian Deadlift
exercises.hint: Put a barbell in front of you on the ground and grab it using a pronated (palms facing down) grip that a little wider than shoulder width. Tip: Depending on the weight used, you may need wrist wraps to perform the exercise and also a raised platform in order to allow for better range of motion.

exercises.name: Romanian Deadlift from Deficit
exercises.hint: Begin standing while holding a bar at arm's length in front of you. You can stand on a raised platform to increase the range of motion.

exercises.name: Rope Climb
exercises.hint: Grab the rope with both hands above your head. Pull down on the rope as you take a small jump.

exercises.name: Rope Crunch
exercises.hint: Kneel 1-2 feet in front of a cable system with a rope attached.

exercises.name: Rope Jumping
exercises.hint: Hold an end of the rope in each hand. Position the rope behind you on the ground. Raise your arms up and turn the rope over your head bringing it down in front of you. When it reaches the ground, jump over it. Find a good turning pace that can be maintained. Different speeds and techniques can be used to introduce variation.

exercises.name: Rope Straight-Arm Pulldown
exercises.hint: Attach a rope to a high pulley and make your weight selection. Stand a couple feet back from the pulley with your feet staggered and take the rope with both hands. Lean forward from the hip, keeping your back straight, with your arms extended up in front of you. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Round The World Shoulder Stretch
exercises.hint: Stand up straight with your legs together, holding a bodybar or broomstick.

exercises.name: Rowing, Stationary
exercises.hint: To begin, seat yourself on the rower. Make sure that your heels are resting comfortably against the base of the foot pedals and that the straps are secured. Select the program that you wish to use, if applicable. Sit up straight and bend forward at the hips.

exercises.name: Runner's Stretch
exercises.hint: It's easiest to get into this stretch if you start standing up, put one leg behind you, and slowly lower your torso down to the floor.

exercises.name: Running, Treadmill
exercises.hint: To begin, step onto the treadmill and select the desired option from the menu. Most treadmills have a manual setting, or you can select a program to run. Typically, you can enter your age and weight to estimate the amount of calories burned during exercise. Elevation can be adjusted to change the intensity of the workout.

exercises.name: Russian Twist
exercises.hint: Lie down on the floor placing your feet either under something that will not move or by having a partner hold them. Your legs should be bent at the knees.

exercises.name: Sandbag Load
exercises.hint: To load sandbags or other objects, begin with the implements placed a distance from the loading platform, typically 50 feet.

exercises.name: Scapular Pull-Up
exercises.hint: Take a pronated grip on a pull-up bar.

exercises.name: Scissor Kick
exercises.hint: To begin, lie down with your back pressed against the floor or on an exercise mat (optional). Your arms should be fully extended to the sides with your palms facing down. Note: The arms should be stationary the entire time.

exercises.name: Scissors Jump
exercises.hint: Assume a lunge stance position with one foot forward with the knee bent, and the rear knee nearly touching the ground.

exercises.name: Seated Band Hamstring Curl
exercises.hint: Secure a band close to the ground and place a bench a couple feet away from it.

exercises.name: Seated Barbell Military Press
exercises.hint: Sit on a Military Press Bench with a bar behind your head and either have a spotter give you the bar (better on the rotator cuff this way) or pick it up yourself carefully with a pronated grip (palms facing forward). Tip: Your grip should be wider than shoulder width and it should create a 90-degree angle between the forearm and the upper arm as the barbell goes down.

exercises.name: Seated Barbell Twist
exercises.hint: Start out by sitting at the end of a flat bench with a barbell placed on top of your thighs. Your feet should be shoulder width apart from each other.

exercises.name: Seated Bent-Over One-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Sit down at the end of a flat bench with a dumbbell in one arm using a neutral grip (palms of the hand facing you).

exercises.name: Seated Bent-Over Rear Delt Raise
exercises.hint: Place a couple of dumbbells looking forward in front of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Seated Bent-Over Two-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Sit down at the end of a flat bench with a dumbbell in both arms using a neutral grip (palms of the hand facing you).

exercises.name: Seated Biceps
exercises.hint: Sit on the floor with your knees bent and your partner standing behind you. Extend your arms straight behind you with your palms facing each other. Your partner will hold your wrists for you. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Cable Rows
exercises.hint: For this exercise you will need access to a low pulley row machine with a V-bar. Note: The V-bar will enable you to have a neutral grip where the palms of your hands face each other. To get into the starting position, first sit down on the machine and place your feet on the front platform or crossbar provided making sure that your knees are slightly bent and not locked.

exercises.name: Seated Cable Shoulder Press
exercises.hint: Adjust the weight to an appropriate amount and be seated, grasping the handles. Your upper arms should be about 90 degrees to the body, with your head and chest up. The elbows should also be bent to about 90 degrees. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Calf Raise
exercises.hint: Sit on the machine and place your toes on the lower portion of the platform provided with the heels extending off. Choose the toe positioning of your choice (forward, in, or out) as per the beginning of this chapter.

exercises.name: Seated Calf Stretch
exercises.hint: Sit up straight on an exercise mat.

exercises.name: Seated Close-Grip Concentration Barbell Curl
exercises.hint: Sit down on a flat bench with a barbell or E-Z Bar in front of you in between your legs. Your legs should be spread with the knees bent and the feet on the floor.

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Curl
exercises.hint: Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell on each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso.

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Inner Biceps Curl
exercises.hint: Sit on the end of a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand being held at arms length. The elbows should be close to the torso.

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Palms-Down Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Start out by placing two dumbbells on the floor in front of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Palms-Up Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Start out by placing two dumbbells on the floor in front of a flat bench.

exercises.name: Seated Dumbbell Press
exercises.hint: Grab a couple of dumbbells and sit on a military press bench or a utility bench that has a back support on it as you place the dumbbells upright on top of your thighs.

exercises.name: Seated Flat Bench Leg Pull-In
exercises.hint: Sit on a bench with the legs stretched out in front of you slightly below parallel and your arms holding on to the sides of the bench. Your torso should be leaning backwards around a 45-degree angle from the bench. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Floor Hamstring Stretch
exercises.hint: Sit on a mat with your right leg extended in front of you and your left leg bent with your foot against your right inner thigh.

exercises.name: Seated Front Deltoid
exercises.hint: Sit upright on the floor with your legs bent, your partner standing behind you. Stick your arms straight out to your sides, with your palms facing the ground. Attempt to move them as far behind you as possible, as your assistant holds your wrists. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Glute
exercises.hint: In a seated position with your knees bent, cross one ankle over the opposite knee. Your partner will stand behind you. Now, lean forward as your partner braces your shoulders with their hands. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Good Mornings
exercises.hint: Set up a box in a power rack. The pins should be set at an appropriate height. Begin by stepping under the bar and placing it across the back of the shoulders, not on top of your traps. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and rotate your elbows forward, attempting to bend the bar across your shoulders.

exercises.name: Seated Hamstring
exercises.hint: In a seated position with your legs extended, have your partner stand behind you. Now, lean forward as your partner braces your shoulders with their hands. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Hamstring and Calf Stretch
exercises.hint: Loop a belt, rope, or band around one foot. Sit down with both legs extended . This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Head Harness Neck Resistance
exercises.hint: Place a neck strap on the floor at the end of a flat bench. Once you have selected the weights, sit at the end of the flat bench with your feet wider than shoulder width apart from each other. Your toes should be pointed out.

exercises.name: Seated Leg Curl
exercises.hint: Adjust the machine lever to fit your height and sit on the machine with your back against the back support pad.

exercises.name: Seated Leg Tucks
exercises.hint: Sit on a bench with the legs stretched out in front of you slightly below parallel and your arms holding on to the sides of the bench. Your torso should be leaning backwards around a 45-degree angle from the bench. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated One-arm Cable Pulley Rows
exercises.hint: To get into the starting position, first sit down on the machine and place your feet on the front platform or crossbar provided making sure that your knees are slightly bent and not locked.

exercises.name: Seated One-Arm Dumbbell Palms-Down Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in your right hand.

exercises.name: Seated One-Arm Dumbbell Palms-Up Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in your right hand.

exercises.name: Seated Overhead Stretch
exercises.hint: Sit up straight on an exercise mat.

exercises.name: Seated Palm-Up Barbell Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Hold a barbell with both hands and your palms facing up; hands spaced about shoulder width.

exercises.name: Seated Palms-Down Barbell Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Hold a barbell with both hands and your palms facing down; hands spaced about shoulder width.

exercises.name: Seated Side Lateral Raise
exercises.hint: Pick a couple of dumbbells and sit at the end of a flat bench with your feet firmly on the floor. Hold the dumbbells with your palms facing in and your arms straight down at your sides at arms' length. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Triceps Press
exercises.hint: Sit down on a bench with back support and grasp a dumbbell with both hands and hold it overhead at arm's length. Tip: a better way is to have somebody hand it to you especially if it is very heavy. The resistance should be resting in the palms of your hands with your thumbs around it. The palm of the hand should be facing inward. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Seated Two-Arm Palms-Up Low-Pulley Wrist Curl
exercises.hint: Put a bench in front of a low pulley machine that has a barbell or EZ Curl attachment on it.

exercises.name: See-Saw Press (Alternating Side Press)
exercises.hint: Grab a dumbbell with each hand and stand up erect.

exercises.name: Shotgun Row
exercises.hint: Attach a single handle to a low cable.

exercises.name: Shoulder Circles
exercises.hint: With shoulders relaxed and arms resting loosely at your sides (or in your lap if you're seated), gently roll your shoulders forward, up, back, and down.

exercises.name: Shoulder Press - With Bands
exercises.hint: To begin, stand on an exercise band so that tension begins at arm's length. Grasp the handles and lift them so that the hands are at shoulder height at each side.

exercises.name: Shoulder Raise
exercises.hint: Relax your arms to your sides and raise your shoulders up toward your ears, then back down.

exercises.name: Shoulder Stretch
exercises.hint: Reach your left arm across your body and hold it straight.

exercises.name: Side Hop-Sprint
exercises.hint: Stand to the side of a cone or hurdle.

exercises.name: Side Lateral Raise
exercises.hint: Pick a couple of dumbbells and stand with a straight torso and the dumbbells by your side at arms length with the palms of the hand facing you. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Side Laterals to Front Raise
exercises.hint: In a standing position, hold a pair of dumbbells at your side. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Side Leg Raises
exercises.hint: Stand next to a chair, which you may hold onto as a support. Stand on one leg. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Side-Lying Floor Stretch
exercises.hint: First lie on your left side, bending your left knee in front of you to stabilize your torso (use your abdominal muscles as well to hold you upright).

exercises.name: Side Lying Groin Stretch
exercises.hint: Start off by lying on your right side and bend your right knee in front of you to stabilize the torso.

exercises.name: Side Neck Stretch
exercises.hint: Start with your shoulders relaxed, gently tilt your head towards your shoulder.

exercises.name: Side Standing Long Jump
exercises.hint: Begin standing with your feet hip width apart in an athletic stance. Your head and chest should be up, knees and hips slightly bent. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Side to Side Box Shuffle
exercises.hint: Stand to one side of the box with your left foot resting on the middle of it.

exercises.name: Side To Side Chins
exercises.hint: Grab the pull-up bar with the palms facing forward using a wide grip.

exercises.name: Side Wrist Pull
exercises.hint: This stretch works best standing. Cross your left arm over the midline of your body and hold the left wrist in your right hand down at the level of your hips. Start the stretch with a bent left arm.

exercises.name: Single-Arm Cable Crossover
exercises.hint: Begin by moving the pulleys to the high position, select the resistance to be used, and take a handle in each hand.

exercises.name: Single-Arm Linear Jammer
exercises.hint: Position a bar into a landmine or securely anchor it in a corner. Load the bar to an appropriate weight.

exercises.name: Single-Arm Push-Up
exercises.hint: Begin laying prone on the ground. Move yourself into a position supporting your weight on your toes and one arm. Your working arm should be placed directly under the shoulder, fully extended. Your legs should be extended, and for this movement you may need a wider base, placing your feet further apart than in a normal push-up.

exercises.name: Single-Cone Sprint Drill
exercises.hint: This drill teaches quick foot action. You need a single cone. Begin standing next to the cone with one arm back and one arm forward.

exercises.name: Single Dumbbell Raise
exercises.hint: With a wide stance, hold a dumbell with both hands, grasping the head of the dumbbell instead of the handle. Your arms should be extended and hanging at the waist. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Single Leg Butt Kick
exercises.hint: Begin by standing on one leg, with the bent knee raised. This will be your start position.

exercises.name: Single Leg Glute Bridge
exercises.hint: Lay on the floor with your feet flat and knees bent.

exercises.name: Single-Leg High Box Squat
exercises.hint: Position a box in a rack. Secure a band or rope in place above the box.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Hop Progression
exercises.hint: Arrange a line of cones in front of you. Assume a relaxed standing position, balanced on one leg. Raise the knee of your opposite leg. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Lateral Hop
exercises.hint: Stand to the side of a cone or hurdle. To get into the start position, stand on one leg with your knee slightly bent.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Leg Extension
exercises.hint: Seat yourself in the machine and adjust it so that you are positioned properly. The pad should be against the lower part of the shin but not in contact with the ankle. Adjust the seat so that the pivot point is in line with your knee. Select a weight appropriate for your abilities.

exercises.name: Single Leg Push-off
exercises.hint: Stand on the ground with one foot resting on the box, heel close to the edge.

exercises.name: Single-Leg Stride Jump
exercises.hint: Stand to the side of a box with your inside foot on top of it, close to the edge.

exercises.name: Sit Squats
exercises.hint: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Sit-Up
exercises.hint: Lie down on the floor placing your feet either under something that will not move or by having a partner hold them. Your legs should be bent at the knees.

exercises.name: Skating
exercises.hint: Roller skating is a fun activity which can be effective in improving cardiorespiratory fitness and muscular endurance. It requires relatively good balance and coordination. It is necessary to learn the basics of skating including turning and stopping and to wear protective gear to avoid possible injury.

exercises.name: Sled Drag - Harness
exercises.hint: To begin, load the sled with the desired weight and attach the pulling strap. You can pull with handles, use a harness, or attach the pulling strap to a weight belt.

exercises.name: Sled Overhead Backward Walk
exercises.hint: Attach dual handles to a sled connected by a rope or chain. Load the sled to a light weight.

exercises.name: Sled Overhead Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: Attach dual handles to a sled using a chain or rope. Load the sled to an appropriate load.

exercises.name: Sled Push
exercises.hint: Load your pushing sled with the desired weight.

exercises.name: Sled Reverse Flye
exercises.hint: Attach dual handles to a sled connected by a rope or chain. Load the sled to a light weight.

exercises.name: Sled Row
exercises.hint: Attach dual handles to a sled connected by a rope or chain. Load the sled to an appropriate weight. Face the sled, backing up until there is some tension in the line.

exercises.name: Sledgehammer Swings
exercises.hint: You will need a tire and a sledgehammer for this exercise. Stand in front of the tire about two feet away from it with a staggered stance. Grip the sledgehammer.

exercises.name: Smith Incline Shoulder Raise
exercises.hint: Place an incline bench underneath the smith machine. Place the barbell at a height that you can reach when lying down and your arms are almost fully extended. Once the weight you need is selected, lie down on the incline bench and make sure your shoulders are aligned right under the barbell.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Behind the Back Shrug
exercises.hint: With the bar at thigh level, load an appropriate weight.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Bent Over Row
exercises.hint: Set the barbell attached to the smith machine to a height that is about 2 inches below your knees.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Calf Raise
exercises.hint: Place a block or weight plate below the bar on the Smith machine. Set the bar to a position that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step onto the plates with the balls of your feet and place the bar on the back of your shoulders.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Close-Grip Bench Press
exercises.hint: Place a flat bench underneath the smith machine. Place the barbell at a height that you can reach when lying down and your arms are almost fully extended. Once the weight you need is selected, lie down on the flat bench. Using a close and pronated grip (palms facing forward) that is around shoulder width, unlock the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Decline Press
exercises.hint: Position a decline bench in the rack so that the bar will be above your chest. Load an appropriate weight and take your place on the bench.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Hang Power Clean
exercises.hint: Position the bar at knee height and load it to an appropriate weight.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Incline Bench Press
exercises.hint: Place an incline bench underneath the smith machine. Place the barbell at a height that you can reach when lying down and your arms are almost fully extended. Once the weight you need is selected, lie down on the incline bench and make sure your upper chest is aligned with the barbell. Using a pronated grip (palms facing forward) that is wider than shoulder width, unlock the bar from the rack and hold it straight over you with your arms locked. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Leg Press
exercises.hint: Position a Smith machine bar a couple feet off of the ground. Ensure that it is resting on the safeties. After loading the bar to an appropriate weight, lie underneath the bar. Place the middle of your feet on the bar, tucking your knees to your chest. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Smith Machine One-Arm Upright Row
exercises.hint: With the bar at thigh level, load an appropriate weight.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Pistol Squat
exercises.hint: To begin, first set the bar to a position that best matches your height. Step under it and position the bar across the back of your shoulders.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Reverse Calf Raises
exercises.hint: Adjust the barbell on the smith machine to fit your height and align a raised platform right under the bar.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Squat
exercises.hint: To begin, first set the bar on the height that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck) across it.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Stiff-Legged Deadlift
exercises.hint: To begin, set the bar on the smith machine to a height that is around the middle of your thighs. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, grasp the bar using a pronated (palms forward) grip that is shoulder width apart. You may need some wrist wraps if using a significant amount of weight.

exercises.name: Smith Machine Upright Row
exercises.hint: To begin, set the bar on the smith machine to a height that is around the middle of your thighs. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, grasp the bar using a pronated (palms forward) grip that is shoulder width apart. You may need some wrist wraps if using a significant amount of weight.

exercises.name: Snatch
exercises.hint: Place your feet at a shoulder width stance with the barbell resting right above the connection between the toes and the rest of the foot.

exercises.name: Snatch Balance
exercises.hint: Begin with the feet in the pulling position, the bar racked across the back of the shoulders, and the hands placed in a wide snatch grip.

exercises.name: Snatch Deadlift
exercises.hint: The snatch deadlift strengthens the first pull of the snatch. Begin with a wide snatch grip with the barbell placed on the platform. The feet should be directly under the hips, with the feet turned out. Squat down to the bar, keeping the back in absolute extension with the head facing forward.

exercises.name: Snatch from Blocks
exercises.hint: Begin with a loaded barbell on boxes or stands of the desired height. A wide grip should be taken on the bar. The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar, with the elbows pointed out. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Snatch Pull
exercises.hint: With a barbell on the floor close to the shins, take a wide snatch grip. Lower your hips with the weight focused on the heels, back straight, head facing forward, chest up, with your shoulders just in front of the bar. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Snatch Shrug
exercises.hint: Begin with a wide grip, with the bar hanging at the mid thigh position. You can use a hook or overhand grip. Your back should be straight and inclined slightly forward.

exercises.name: Speed Band Overhead Triceps
exercises.hint: For this exercise anchor a band to the ground. We used an incline bench and anchored the band to the base, standing over the bench. Alternatively, this could be performed standing on the band.

exercises.name: Speed Box Squat
exercises.hint: Attach bands to the bar that are securely anchored near the ground. You may need to choke the bands to get adequate tension.

exercises.name: Speed Squats
exercises.hint: This exercise is best performed inside a squat rack for safety purposes. To begin, first set the bar on a rack that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck) across it.

exercises.name: Spell Caster
exercises.hint: Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a pronated grip. Your feet should be wide with your hips and knees extended. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Spider Crawl
exercises.hint: Begin in a prone position on the floor. Support your weight on your hands and toes, with your feet together and your body straight. Your arms should be bent to 90 degrees. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Spinal Stretch
exercises.hint: Sit in a chair so your back is straight and your feet planted on the floor.

exercises.name: Split Clean
exercises.hint: With a barbell on the floor close to the shins, take an overhand grip just outside the legs. Lower your hips with the weight focused on the heels, back straight, head facing forward, chest up, with your shoulders just in front of the bar. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Split Jerk
exercises.hint: Standing with the weight racked on the front of the shoulders, begin with the dip. With your feet directly under your hips, flex the knees without moving the hips backward.

exercises.name: Split Jump
exercises.hint: Assume a lunge stance position with one foot forward with the knee bent, and the rear knee nearly touching the ground.

exercises.name: Split Snatch
exercises.hint: Begin with a loaded barbell on the floor. The bar should be close to or touching the shins, and a wide grip should be taken on the bar. The feet should be directly below the hips, with the feet turned out as needed. Lower the hips, with the chest up and the head looking forward. The shoulders should be just in front of the bar. This will be the starting position.

exercises.name: Split Squat with Dumbbells
exercises.hint: Position yourself into a staggered stance with the rear foot elevated and front foot forward.

exercises.name: Split Squats
exercises.hint: Being in a standing position. Jump into a split leg position, with one leg forward and one leg back, flexing the knees and lowering your hips slightly as you do so.

exercises.name: Squat Jerk
exercises.hint: Standing with the weight racked on the front of the shoulders, begin with the dip. With your feet directly under your hips, flex the knees without moving the hips backward. Go down only slightly, and reverse direction as powerfully as possible. Drive through the heels create as much speed and force as possible, and be sure to move your head out of the way as the bar leaves the shoulders.

exercises.name: Squat with Bands
exercises.hint: Set up the bands on the sleeves, secured to either band pegs, the rack, or dumbbells so that there is appropriate tension.

exercises.name: Squat with Chains
exercises.hint: To set up the chains, begin by looping the leader chain over the sleeves of the bar. The heavy chain should be attached using a snap hook. Adjust the length of the lead chain so that a few links are still on the floor at the top of the movement.

exercises.name: Squat with Plate Movers
exercises.hint: To begin, first set the bar on a rack to just below shoulder level. Position a weight plate on the ground a couple feet back from the rack. Once the bar is loaded, step under it and place the back of your shoulders across it.

exercises.name: Squats - With Bands
exercises.hint: To start out, make sure that the exercise band is at an even split between both the left and right side of the body. To do this, use your hands to grab both sides of the band and place both feet in the middle of the band. Your feet should be shoulder width apart from each other.

exercises.name: Stairmaster
exercises.hint: To begin, step onto the stairmaster and select the desired option from the menu. You can choose a manual setting, or you can select a program to run. Typically, you can enter your age and weight to estimate the amount of calories burned during exercise.

exercises.name: Standing Alternating Dumbbell Press
exercises.hint: Stand with a dumbbell in each hand. Raise the dumbbells to your shoulders with your palms facing forward and your elbows pointed out. This will be your starting position.

exercises.name: Standing Barbell Calf Raise
exercises.hint: This exercise is best performed inside a squat rack for safety purposes. To begin, first set the bar on a rack that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place the bar on the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck).

exercises.name: Standing Barbell Press Behind Neck
exercises.hint: This exercise is best performed inside a squat rack for easier pick up of the bar. To begin, first set the bar on a rack that best matches your height. Once the correct height is chosen and the bar is loaded, step under the bar and place the back of your shoulders (slightly below the neck) across it.

exercises.name: Standing Bent-Over One-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: With a dumbbell in one hand and the palm facing your torso, bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight until it is almost parallel to the floor. Make sure that you keep the head up.

exercises.name: Standing Bent-Over Two-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension
exercises.hint: With a dumbbell in each hand and the palms facing your torso, bend your knees slightly and bring your torso forward, by bending at the waist, while keeping the back straight until it is almost parallel to the floor. Make sure that you keep the head up. The upper arms should be close to the torso and parallel to the floor while the forearms are pointing towards the floor as the hands hold the weights. Tip: There should be a 90-degree angle between the forearms and the upper arm. This is your starting position.

exercises.name: Standing Biceps Cable Curl
